arn.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Routing Profile.

defaultOutboundQueueId.description: Specifies the default outbound queue for the Routing Profile.

description.description: Specifies the description of the Routing Profile.

instanceId.description: Specifies the identifier of the hosting Amazon Connect Instance.

mediaConcurrencies.description: One or more `media_concurrencies` blocks that specify the channels that agents can handle in the Contact Control Panel (CCP) for this Routing Profile. The `media_concurrencies` block is documented below.

name.description: Specifies the name of the Routing Profile.

queueConfigs.description: One or more `queue_configs` blocks that specify the inbound queues associated with the routing profile. If no queue is added, the agent only can make outbound calls. The `queue_configs` block is documented below.

routingProfileId.description: The identifier for the Routing Profile.

tags.description:
Tags to apply to the Routing Profile. If configured with a provider
`default_tags` configuration block present, tags with matching keys will overwrite those defined at the provider-level.

tagsAll.description: A map of tags assigned to the resource, including those inherited from the provider `default_tags` configuration block.
